Introduction
The graph illustrates changes in the percentage of tourist to Scotland who visited four various points of interest from 1980 to 2010.

Overall, the figure for Castle and Zoo improved marginally while that for Aquarium and Festival declined.
Main body 1
Zoo and Castle recorded increases
Over the study period. Starting at twenty two percent, the proportion of tourist visited Castle experienced a moderate growth to 4% from 1980 to 1985 and this was followed by dramatic escalate and hit the highest level to approximately 45 percent.
Zoo rose minimally to 20 percent in 2010 at the and of the period.
Main body 2
In contrast the rest of the category had relatively small proportions
Festival experienced a consistent drop to in 2010 by 11 percent. The figure for Aquarium saw a remarkable growth well over to 30% in 1985 but this was followed by steeply plummeted in 2010 by 16 percent over the following decade.
